TITLE: Initializing Dropdowns with Select2 using Local Array Data in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to initialize dropdown menus by supplying an array of items directly to the Select2 library. Dependencies include the Select2 library and a DOM with select elements. The key parameters are arrays of objects representing each item to be included in the dropdown. The snippet provides a straightforward way to populate select elements, immediately rendering items as `<option>` elements and maintaining the backward compatibility with Select2 v3.5.
SOURCE: https://github.com/select2/select2/blob/develop/docs/pages/06.data-sources/03.arrays/docs.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
var data = [
    {
        id: 0,
        text: 'enhancement'
    },
    {
        id: 1,
        text: 'bug'
    },
    {
        id: 2,
        text: 'duplicate'
    },
    {
        id: 3,
        text: 'invalid'
    },
    {
        id: 4,
        text: 'wontfix'
    }
];

$(".js-example-data-array").select2({
  data: data
})

$(".js-example-data-array-selected").select2({
  data: data
})
```

